    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "idk, \"adaptation\" sounds a bit vague lol. like, can a 50 year old guy who's spent his whole life in a coal mine really just pivot to installing solar panels? it feels like the people writing these bills don't really care about the people losing their livelihoods as long as they hit their climate goals. is it even possible to be \"fair\" to the coal towns when the whole point of the bill is to move away from them?",
