      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are right that the transition is far more complex than simply \"adapting,\" and the human cost in coal communities is a huge ethical challenge. True fairness requires robust, targeted economic support beyond just job training, such as infrastructure investment and diversification grants for entire towns. The debate often hinges on whether the short-term pain of the transition is an acceptable cost for long-term environmental and energy security benefits.",
